'''[[Osteonecrosis]] of the [[jaw]]''' ('''ONJ''') is a severe [[bone]] disease that affects the [[maxilla]] and the [[Human mandible|mandible]]. Various forms of ONJ have been described over the last 160 years, and a number of causes have been suggested in the literature.
Osteonecrosis of the jaws associated with bisphosphonate therapy, required by some cancer treatment regimens, has been identified and defined as a pathological entity since 2003.<ref name="RevistaOMF">
